            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Numbers 18:1-7",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", Elevated by success, Uzziah appears to have desired to become supreme pontiff as well as king, and to exercise the same dual functions as the Egyptian Pharaohs were wont to do. Some have thought that he merely revived the precedent of David and Solomon; but it can hardly be proved that those monarchs, though represented as organising the priesthood and ritual, and conducting great religious festivals, ever actually performed the distinctive functions of priests. (Comp. the conduct of Saul, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Samuel 13:9",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
